          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "High purity Sc2O3 powder (>99.5%) pressed into pellets.",
                "Al foils 10 microns to wrap the pallets and 100 microns",
                "for support (backing). Ti 12 microns monitor foils.",
                "The effective Sc thickness 285 - 303 microns."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "High purity Ge gamma spectrometer"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "BCINT",
                "EDEG",
                "EXTB",
                "GSPEC",
                "MOSEP",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "One stack containing 10 pellets, together with",
                "interleaved natTi monitor foils in Faraday-cup like",
                "target holder equipped with a collimator (5 mm) and a",
                "secondary electron suppresser was irradiated with",
                "protons in the external beam of the VUB-Cyclotron",
                "CGR-560 at 38 MeV, 115 nA for 2 h.",
                "The monitor reaction natTi(p,n)48V was used to",
                "determine the effective beam current (115 nA) and the",
                "energy that was downshifted by 0.3 MeV.",
                "The mean energy for each foil in the stack was",
                "calculated with the SRIM 2006 program.",
                "No chemical separation was used.",
                "Measurement started shortly after EOB and decay was",
                "followed by measuring the samples several times.",
                "Excitation functions were determined relative to the",
                "simultaneously re-measured monitor reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
